In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims January 18, 2016, as the Martin Luther King Jr. Federal Holiday. He highlights the importance of Dr. King's non-violent movement and his belief in expanding freedom and equal opportunity for all. The President acknowledges the work that still needs to be done to address injustice and inequality in America, such as poverty, inadequate resources in schools, and hunger. He urges Americans to recognize the common humanity of all people, regardless of race or background. The President encourages citizens to observe the holiday through civic, community, and service projects in honor of Dr. King.